{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, in Mayer et al. 's (1995) trust model, the trustworthiness dimensions of ability and benevolence align closely with the competence and warmth dimensions in the SCM, respectively.",
    "Therefore, warmth and competence may be two core components of trustworthiness affecting interpersonal trust.",
    "The significance of these two dimensions is evident in their substantial influence on individuals' evaluations and behaviors toward others (Mayer et al., 1995; Fiske, 2012).",
    "Competence is the key factor influencing trust in automation (Drnec et al., 2016).",
    "When users observe errors in the automated system, their trust in it decreases, leading them to monitor the system more closely (Muir and Moray, 1996)."
  ]
}